'''''Atlantic Balloon Crossing''''' is a video game written by Dean Powell for the [[TRS-80]] and published by [[The Software Exchange]] in 1979. It was originally printed as a type-in [[BASIC]] listing in the June 1979 issue of ''[[SoftSide]]'' magazine.<ref name="softside">{{cite journal |last1=Powell |first1=Dean |title=Atlantic Balloon Crossing |journal=SoftSide |date=June 1979 |issue=9 |page=8 |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-09/page/n7}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Atlantic Balloon Crossing'' is a game in which players control gas balloons to try to cross the Atlantic Ocean starting in Canada to reach Paris in the shortest time possible.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Joseph Suchar reviewed ''Atlantic Balloon Crossing'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 37.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Suchar |first=Joseph |date=March 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=37|pages=27}}</ref> Suchar commented that "I feel that this game is well worth the money. It provides a challenging multi-player or solitaire game which is difficult to optimize."<ref name="SG"/>

